text:
Has Pres. Trump done enough to tamp down anti-Semitism?

@RepLizCheney: "I don't believe this is right or left, this is an issue on which all of us should come together."

#MTP

Role of congress to strip committee assignments? (re: Reps. King, Omar) 

@RepLizCheney: "Nobody is going to say we're going to expel them...but there are things that shouldn't be part of our public discourse," referring to white supremacy and anti-Semitism

#MTP

Why does the President surround himself with people who can't tell the truth to law enforcement or Congress? 

@Jim_Jordan: "The President surrounded himself with some people that maybe he shouldn't, I don't know." 

Adds Manafort worked in GOP politics before the Trump campaign

Should working with WikiLeaks be a crime?

@marcorubio tells me, "I think certainly if you're wittingly doing it, it should be considered as such."

#MTP

Is impeachment talk a distraction for Democrats? 

@LeaderHoyer: "Impeachment talks right now are a distraction, we'll have to see what the Mueller report says." Says priority right now is opening the government.

#MTP

Is DACA for the wall still on the table?

@SenatorDurbin: "I touched that hot stove back in February...President's word didn't stand up when we basically got down to real bargaining" on DACA

#MTP

Has @SenToomey run out of patience with Pres. Trump?

@SenToomey: "I'm still in the mode of working with the President where I can" and trying to persuade him at other times

#MTP

